This is a very simple recipe that turns out well. I reduced the overall portion to make it for one person and substituted mussels and shrimp for some of the clams. I was very pleased with the results.

Rating: 3
Loved the smokiness of the bacon with the clams and the speed it went together. We added some crushed red pepper with the garlic for a little kick. Next time I make it I will drain the tomatoes and add the liquid in gradually as there was a lot of broth. Almost too much for the crusty bread.

Rating: 3
This is a very good quick & easy weeknight recipe. My only change was to substitute dried herbes de provence for the parsley as I had no fresh parsley on hand. I can imagine it being even better with fresh tomatoes & fresh basil from my garden this summer. I made soup out of the leftovers -- pureed the broth & added a little half & half, chopped the clams & added them at the last minute. Yummmm!

